hwGponMIB.name: hwGponMIB

revisions.description: V1.21, changes in this revision: - Modify the node hwGonuPasswordChangeTrap name to hwGonuAuthChangeTrap.
V1.20, changes in this revision: - Add parameters for the trap node hwGonuAuthChangeTrap.
V1.19, changes in this revision: - Delete unnecessary en dashes.
V1.18, changes in this revision: - Add leaf node hwGonuTxDiscardedFrames in table hwGonuStatisticsTable.
V1.17, changes in this revision: - Add leaf node hwGonuLoid, hwGonuCheckCode in table hwGonuAuthTable for config the loid and checkcode value of ONU.
V1.16, changes in this revision: - Add leaf node hwGonuPsk in table hwGonuAuthTable for config and obtain the hex value of PSK.

V1.15, changes in this revision: - Add leaf node hwXponNNIUplinkMode in table hwGponNNICfg for config uplink mode of PON NNI port. - Modify the description hwTimeElapsed to hwGponTimeElapsed, and hwValidInterval to hwGponValidInterval.

V1.14, changes in this revision: - Add leaf node hwGonuOpticsModuleType, hwGonuOpticsModuleSubType, hwGonuOpticsModuleUsedType, hwGonuOpticsModuleEncapsulationType in table hwGonuStatusTable for obtaining optical-module information.
V1.12, changes in this revision: - modify the description of the whole MIB file. - add leaf node hwGonuClearThreshold in table hwGonuAlarmThresholdTable for clear optical-module threshold.

V1.11, changes in this revision: - Add the definition of the trap node, include:hwGonuLinkMISRestoreTrap, hwGonuLinkPEERestoreTrap,hwGonuTempExceedThreAlarmTrap, hwGonuTempExceedThreRestoreAlarmTrap, hwGonuVoltExceedThreAlarmTrap, hwGonuVoltExceedThreRestoreAlarmTrap, hwGonuBiasExceedThreAlarmTrap, hwGonuBiasExceedThreRestoreAlarmTrap, hwGonuTxPowerExceedThreAlarmTrap, hwGonuTxPowerExceedThreRestoreAlarmTrap, hwGonuRxPowerExceedThreRestoreAlarmTrap, hwGonuRxPowerExceedThreAlarmTrap, hwGonuROGUEOntFailAlarmTrap, hwGonuROGUEOntRestoreAlarmTrap, hwGponnniOntLinkLosAlarmTrap, hwGponnniOntLinkLofAlarmTrap, hwGponnniOntLinkSfAlarmTrap, hwGponnniOntLinkSdAlarmTrap, hwGponnniOntLinkLcdgFailAlarmTrap, hwGponnniOntLinkSufFailAlarmTrap, hwGponnniOntLinkLosRestoreAlarmTrap, hwGponnniOntLinkLofRestoreAlarmTrap, hwGponnniOntLinkSfRestoreAlarmTrap, hwGponnniOntLinkSdRestoreAlarmTrap, hwGponnniOntLinkLcdgRestoreAlarmTrap, hwGponnniOntLinkSufRestoreAlarmTrap, hwGonuAuthChangeTrap. add leaf node hwGonuOperType in table hwGonuTrapsVbOids for trap optimization. - Extend the value of several leaves to '-1', such as hwGonuRogueOntState and hwGonuStatisticsClear.
V1.10, changes in this revision: - Modify chinese character and module name.
V1.09, changes in this revision: - Modify the errors of the MIB file for MIB standardization.

V1.08, changes in this revision: - Add leaf nodes hwGonuRxFrames, hwGonuPonRxOctetsCnt, hwGonuRxUnicastFrames, hwGonuRxMulticastFrames, hwGonuRxBroadcastFrames, hwGonuRx64BytesFrames, hwGonuRx65to127BytesFrames, hwGonuRx128to255BytesFrames, hwGonuRx256to511BytesFrames, hwGonuRx512to1023BytesFrames, hwGonuRx1024to1518BytesFrames, hwGonuRxOver1518BytesFrames, hwGonuRxUndersizeFrames, hwGonuRxOversizeFrames, hwGonuRxCrcErrorFrames, hwGonuRxDiscardedFrames, hwGonuTxFrames, hwGonuPonTxOctetsCnt, hwGonuTxUnicastFrames, hwGonuTxMulticastFrames, hwGonuTxBroadcastFrames, hwGonuTx64BytesFrames, hwGonuTx65to127BytesFrames, hwGonuTx128to255BytesFrames, hwGonuTx256to511BytesFrames, hwGonuTx512to1023BytesFrames, hwGonuTx1024to1518BytesFrames, hwGonuTxOver1518BytesFrames, hwGonuPonRxErrFramesCnt and hwGonuTxServiceFramesCnt in table hwGonuStatisticsTable for getting statistics information. - Add leaf nodes hwGonuTxPowerUpperThreshold, hwGonuTxPowerLowerThreshold, hwGonuBiasUpperThreshold, hwGonuBiasLowerThreshold, hwGonuTemperatureUpperThreshold, hwGonuTemperatureLowerThreshold, hwGonuVoltageUpperThreshold and hwGonuVoltageLowerThreshold for setting or obtaining optical module alarm threshold.
V1.07, changes in this revision: - Add the definition of the trap node.

V1.06, changes in this revision: - Add leaf node hwGonuRxAndTxDiscardEthFramesCnt in table hwGonuStatisticsTable for obtaining the count of discarding the Ethernet frames. - Modify the leaf node hwGonuStatisticsClear's access priority from write-only to read-write.

V1.03, changes in this revision: - Add table hwGonuAlarmThresholdTable for setting or obtaining GPON NNI alarm threshold. - Add table hwGponNNIHistoryStatsTable for obtaining GPON NNI history statistics information. - Add table hwGponNNICfgTable for setting or obtaining GPON NNI configuration information. - Add leaf nodes hwGonuRxGemFramesCnt, hwGonuTxGemFramesCnt, hwGonuRxCpuFramesCnt and hwGonuRxDiscardEthFramesCnt in table hwGonuStatisticsTable for obtaining statistics information. - Add leaf nodes hwGonuTxPower, hwGonuRxPower, hwGonuTemperature, hwGonuBiasCurrent, hwGonuVoltage and hwGonuRogueOntState in table hwGonuStatusTable for obtaining GPON NNI state information. - Add notification hwGonuLinkTFTrap for TF alarm. - Add notification hwGonuLinkMEMTrap for MEM alarm.

hwGponMIB.contactinfo: Huawei Industrial Base Bantian, Longgang Shenzhen 518129 People's Republic of China Website: http://www.huawei.com Email: support@huawei.com
hwGponMIB.description: This MIB is used for defining GPON NNI MIB objects. GPON NNI refers to PON interface at ONU.

hwGonuLinkLOSTrap.name: hwGonuLinkLOSTrap
hwGonuLinkLOSTrap.description: This trap is sent when the LOS(Loss of Signal) alarm of GPON ONU occures.

hwGonuLinkLOFTrap.name: hwGonuLinkLOFTrap
hwGonuLinkLOFTrap.description: This trap is sent when the LOF(Loss of Frame) alarm of GPON ONU occures.

hwGonuLinkSFTrap.name: hwGonuLinkSFTrap
hwGonuLinkSFTrap.description: This trap is sent when the SF(Signal Fail) alarm of GPON ONU occures.

hwGonuLinkSDTrap.name: hwGonuLinkSDTrap
hwGonuLinkSDTrap.description: This trap is sent when the SD(Signal Degrade) alarm of GPON ONU occures.

hwGonuLinkLCDGTrap.name: hwGonuLinkLCDGTrap
hwGonuLinkLCDGTrap.description: This trap is sent when the LCDG(Loss of Channel Delineation for GEM) alarm of GPON ONU occures.

hwGonuLinkRDITrap.name: hwGonuLinkRDITrap
hwGonuLinkRDITrap.description: This trap is sent when the RDI(Remote Defect Indication) alarm of GPON ONU occures.

hwGonuLinkSUFTrap.name: hwGonuLinkSUFTrap
hwGonuLinkSUFTrap.description: This trap is sent when the SUF(Start Up Failure) alarm of GPON ONU occures.

hwGonuLinkDACTTrap.name: hwGonuLinkDACTTrap
hwGonuLinkDACTTrap.description: This trap is sent when the DACT(Deactivate (ONU-ID)) alarm of GPON ONU occures.

hwGonuLinkDISTrap.name: hwGonuLinkDISTrap
hwGonuLinkDISTrap.description: This trap is sent when the DIS(Disabled (ONU serial number)) alarm of GPON ONU occures.

hwGonuLinkMISTrap.name: hwGonuLinkMISTrap
hwGonuLinkMISTrap.description: This trap is sent when the MIS((link) Mismatch) alarm of GPON ONU occures.

hwGonuLinkPEETrap.name: hwGonuLinkPEETrap
hwGonuLinkPEETrap.description: This trap is sent when the PEE(Physical Equipment Error) alarm of GPON ONU occures.

hwGonuLinkTFTrap.name: hwGonuLinkTFTrap
hwGonuLinkTFTrap.description: This trap is sent when the TF(Transmitter Failure) alarm of GPON ONU occures.

hwGonuLinkMEMTrap.name: hwGonuLinkMEMTrap
hwGonuLinkMEMTrap.description: This trap is sent when the MEM(Message Error Message) alarm of GPON ONU occures.

hwGonuLinkMISRestoreTrap.name: hwGonuLinkMISRestoreTrap
hwGonuLinkMISRestoreTrap.description: This trap is sent when the link mismatch of ONT(MIS) recovers.

hwGonuLinkPEERestoreTrap.name: hwGonuLinkPEERestoreTrap
hwGonuLinkPEERestoreTrap.description: This trap is sent when the OLT recovers from the physical equipment error.

hwGonuTempExceedThreAlarmTrap.name: hwGonuTempExceedThreAlarmTrap
hwGonuTempExceedThreAlarmTrap.description: This trap is sent when the temperature of GPON optical-module exceeded alarm threshold.

hwGonuTempExceedThreRestoreAlarmTrap.name: hwGonuTempExceedThreRestoreAlarmTrap
hwGonuTempExceedThreRestoreAlarmTrap.description: This trap is sent when the temperature of GPON ONU's optical-module exceeded alarm threshold recoveres.

hwGonuVoltExceedThreAlarmTrap.name: hwGonuVoltExceedThreAlarmTrap
hwGonuVoltExceedThreAlarmTrap.description: This trap is sent when the voltage of GPON ONU's optical-module exceeded alarm threshold.

hwGonuVoltExceedThreRestoreAlarmTrap.name: hwGonuVoltExceedThreRestoreAlarmTrap
hwGonuVoltExceedThreRestoreAlarmTrap.description: This trap is sent when the voltage of GPON ONU's optical-module exceeded alarm threshold recoveres.

hwGonuBiasExceedThreAlarmTrap.name: hwGonuBiasExceedThreAlarmTrap
hwGonuBiasExceedThreAlarmTrap.description: This trap is sent when the bias current of GPON ONU's optical module exceeded alarm threshold.

hwGonuBiasExceedThreRestoreAlarmTrap.name: hwGonuBiasExceedThreRestoreAlarmTrap
hwGonuBiasExceedThreRestoreAlarmTrap.description: This trap is sent when the bias current of GPON ONU's optical module exceeded alarm threshold recoveres.

hwGonuTxPowerExceedThreAlarmTrap.name: hwGonuTxPowerExceedThreAlarmTrap
hwGonuTxPowerExceedThreAlarmTrap.description: This trap is sent when the tx-power of GPON ONU's optical-module exceeded alarm threshold.

hwGonuTxPowerExceedThreRestoreAlarmTrap.name: hwGonuTxPowerExceedThreRestoreAlarmTrap
hwGonuTxPowerExceedThreRestoreAlarmTrap.description: This trap is sent when the tx-power of GPON ONU's optical-module exceeded alarm threshold recoveres.

hwGonuRxPowerExceedThreRestoreAlarmTrap.name: hwGonuRxPowerExceedThreRestoreAlarmTrap
hwGonuRxPowerExceedThreRestoreAlarmTrap.description: This trap is sent when the rx-power of GPON ONU's optical-module exceeded alarm threshold.

hwGonuRxPowerExceedThreAlarmTrap.name: hwGonuRxPowerExceedThreAlarmTrap
hwGonuRxPowerExceedThreAlarmTrap.description: This trap is sent when the rx-power of GPON ONU's optical-module exceeded alarm threshold recoveres.

hwGonuROGUEOntFailAlarmTrap.name: hwGonuROGUEOntFailAlarmTrap
hwGonuROGUEOntFailAlarmTrap.description: This trap is sent when the ONU's optical-module always send laser.

hwGonuROGUEOntRestoreAlarmTrap.name: hwGonuROGUEOntRestoreAlarmTrap
hwGonuROGUEOntRestoreAlarmTrap.description: This trap is sent when the ONU's optical-module always send laser alarm recoveres.

hwGponnniOntLinkLosAlarmTrap.name: hwGponnniOntLinkLosAlarmTrap
hwGponnniOntLinkLosAlarmTrap.description: This trap is sent when the fiber is broken or ONT can not receive any expected optical signals(LOS).

hwGponnniOntLinkLofAlarmTrap.name: hwGponnniOntLinkLofAlarmTrap
hwGponnniOntLinkLofAlarmTrap.description: This trap is sent when the loss of frame (LOF) occurs at the ONT.

hwGponnniOntLinkSfAlarmTrap.name: hwGponnniOntLinkSfAlarmTrap
hwGponnniOntLinkSfAlarmTrap.description: This trap is sent when the signal failed (SF) occurs at the ONT.

hwGponnniOntLinkSdAlarmTrap.name: hwGponnniOntLinkSdAlarmTrap
hwGponnniOntLinkSdAlarmTrap.description: This trap is sent when the signal degrade (SD) occurs at the ONT.

hwGponnniOntLinkLcdgFailAlarmTrap.name: hwGponnniOntLinkLcdgFailAlarmTrap
hwGponnniOntLinkLcdgFailAlarmTrap.description: This trap is sent when the loss of GEM channel delineation (LCDG) occurs at the ONT.

hwGponnniOntLinkSufFailAlarmTrap.name: hwGponnniOntLinkSufFailAlarmTrap
hwGponnniOntLinkSufFailAlarmTrap.description: This trap is sent when the ranging of the ONT failure (SUF) occurs.

hwGponnniOntLinkLosRestoreAlarmTrap.name: hwGponnniOntLinkLosRestoreAlarmTrap
hwGponnniOntLinkLosRestoreAlarmTrap.description: This trap is sent when the loss of signal (LOS) at the ONT recovers.

hwGponnniOntLinkLofRestoreAlarmTrap.name: hwGponnniOntLinkLofRestoreAlarmTrap
hwGponnniOntLinkLofRestoreAlarmTrap.description: This trap is sent when the loss of frame (LOF) at the ONT recovers.

hwGponnniOntLinkSfRestoreAlarmTrap.name: hwGponnniOntLinkSfRestoreAlarmTrap
hwGponnniOntLinkSfRestoreAlarmTrap.description: This trap is sent when the signal failure (SF) at the ONT recovers.

hwGponnniOntLinkSdRestoreAlarmTrap.name: hwGponnniOntLinkSdRestoreAlarmTrap
hwGponnniOntLinkSdRestoreAlarmTrap.description: This trap is sent when the signal degrade (SD) at the ONT recovers.

hwGponnniOntLinkLcdgRestoreAlarmTrap.name: hwGponnniOntLinkLcdgRestoreAlarmTrap
hwGponnniOntLinkLcdgRestoreAlarmTrap.description: This trap is sent when the loss of GEM channel delineation (LCDG) at the ONT recovers.

hwGponnniOntLinkSufRestoreAlarmTrap.name: hwGponnniOntLinkSufRestoreAlarmTrap
hwGponnniOntLinkSufRestoreAlarmTrap.description: This trap is sent when the ranging of ONT failure (SUF) recovers.

hwGonuStatusTable.name: hwGonuStatusTable
hwGonuStatusTable.description: The table hwGonuStatusTable contains configuration and status parameters of the GPON ONU. The index of this table is ifIndex.

hwGonuStatusEntry.name: hwGonuStatusEntry
hwGonuStatusEntry.description: The table hwGonuStatusTable contains configuration and status parameters of the GPON ONU. The index of this entry is ifIndex.

hwGonuLinkStatus.name: hwGonuLinkStatus
hwGonuLinkStatus.description: The port link status, Options: 1.linkDown(1) -Link down 2.linkUp(2) -Link up

hwGonuRegStatus.name: hwGonuRegStatus
hwGonuRegStatus.description: The port register status, Options: 1. registerPass(1) -The port is authenticated successfully 2. registerFail(2) -The port fails to be authenticated

hwGonuRxSpeed.name: hwGonuRxSpeed
hwGonuRxSpeed.description: The port down stream speed. Unit: kbps

hwGonuTxSpeed.name: hwGonuTxSpeed
hwGonuTxSpeed.description: The port up stream speed. Unit: kbps

hwGonuRxBitErr.name: hwGonuRxBitErr
hwGonuRxBitErr.description: The port down stream bit error ratio. Unit: bits/100ms

hwGonuPloamStates.name: hwGonuPloamStates
hwGonuPloamStates.description: The gpon onu PLOAM states. Options: 1. initial(1) -Initial state 2. standby(2) -Standby state 3. serialNumber(3) -Serial_Number state 4. ranging(4) -Ranging state 5. operation(5) -Operation state 6. popUp(6) -POPUP state 7. emergencyStop(7) -Emergency Stop state

hwGonuOmciPortID.name: hwGonuOmciPortID
hwGonuOmciPortID.description: Indicates the ID of the GEM port corresponding to the OMCI.

hwGonuTxPower.name: hwGonuTxPower
hwGonuTxPower.description: The MDU TX power. Unit: 1/100 dBm

hwGonuRxPower.name: hwGonuRxPower
hwGonuRxPower.description: The MDU RX power. Unit: 1/100 dBm

hwGonuTemperature.name: hwGonuTemperature
hwGonuTemperature.description: The MDU Current Temperature. Unit: 1/100 degree centigrade

hwGonuBiasCurrent.name: hwGonuBiasCurrent
hwGonuBiasCurrent.description: The MDU Laser Bias Current. Unit: 1/100 mA

hwGonuRogueOntState.name: hwGonuRogueOntState
hwGonuRogueOntState.description: Indicates whether the optical port is shut down due to the continuous mode(rogue ONU). Options: 1. yes(1) - The optical port is shut down due to the continuous mode 2. no(2) - The optical port is shut down due to other reason 3. invalid(-1) - Invalid value

hwGonuOpticsModuleType.name: hwGonuOpticsModuleType
hwGonuOpticsModuleType.description: This object indicates the type of the optical transceiver. Options: 1. unknown(1) - Unknow 2. gpon(2) - GPON 3. epon(3) - EPON 4. epon10g(4) - 10G EPON 5. gpon10g(5) - 10G GPON 6. wdmpon(6) - WDM PON 7. hybridpon(7)- Hybrid PON 8. gponepon(8) - GPON and EPON 9. invalid(-1) - Indicates that the query fails or no information is detected

hwGonuOpticsModuleSubType.name: hwGonuOpticsModuleSubType
hwGonuOpticsModuleSubType.description: This object indicates the sub type of the optical transceiver. Options: 1.unknown(1) - Unknow 2.classbplus(101) - CLASS B+ 3.classcplus(102) - CLASS C+ 4.classb(103) - CLASS B 5.px20(201) - PX20 6.px20plus(202) - PX20+ 7.pr30(301) - PR30 8.pr20(302) - PR20 9.prx30(303) - PRX30 10.prx20(304) - PRX20 11.classbplusandpx20plus(701) - CLASS B+ and PX20+ 12.invalid(-1) - Indicates that the query fails or no information is detected

hwGonuOpticsModuleUsedType.name: hwGonuOpticsModuleUsedType
hwGonuOpticsModuleUsedType.description: This object indicates the application scenario of the optical transceiver. Options: 1.unknown(1) - Unknow 2.olt(2) - OLT 3.onu(4) - ONU 4.invalid(-1) - Indicates that the query fails or no information is detected

hwGonuOpticsModuleEncapsulationType.name: hwGonuOpticsModuleEncapsulationType
hwGonuOpticsModuleEncapsulationType.description: This object indicates the encapsulation information about the optical transceiver. Options: 1. unknown(1) - Unknown 2. sff2x5(2) - SFF 2x5 3. sff2x10(3) - SFF 2x10 4. sfp(4) - SFP 5. xfp(5) - XFP 6. lxfp(6) - LXFP 7. bosaonboard(7)- BOSA ON BOARD 8. invalid(-1) - Indicates that the query fails or no information is detected
